29/03/2009
MADRID, Spain -- Spanish police have detained a alleged senior official of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK), authorities announced on Friday (March 27th). The suspect is Remzi Kartal, a former lawmaker from Turkey's disbanded Democracy Party (DEP) and allegedly a former PKK commander. He was apprehended last Monday in a Madrid shopping mall. Media quoted diplomatic sources as saying the Turkish Embassy in Madrid will request Kartal's extradition to Turkey as soon as possible. (Hurriyet, Yeni Safak - 28/03/07, Anadolu news agency, NTV, TRT - 27/03/09)
